Overall Rating Scale
1 = serious issues with data, i.e.participant found out their parent was ill during the session, all the tasks failed, participant was asleep etc.
2 = 40-60 % of the data/session had problems
3 = A couple of small problems but overall good
4 = One small problem
5 = Dont need to talk about it :) Session was perfect!

After taking the USB out and putting it back in, it worked fine. The participants head moved out of the eye-tracking frame during the Pavphase of DTK, the Pav phase of mushrooms, there PIT phase of mushrooms, the instrumental phase of Vending machine, and twice during the PIT phase of vending machine. I think the issue was the eye-tracker, not the participant, because the next participant had the same problem, and because, at one point, she had moved her head all the way to one side of the chin rest and she still needed to move it more to that side to be in the frame. had to try numerous times (maybe 8 or 9) to calibrate eye-tracking for the instrumental phase of VM. I ended up accepting a calibration that was generally good, except that one point (towards the left) was off by 1.61 . She had glasses the gave off a cornea-like reflection, so maybe that was causing the difficulty. Since we had so much difficulty getting a good calibration for instrumental, I accepted a calibration with a .76 average and .90 max for the Pav phase of VM.
